The paper deals with the problem of mining predictive complex temporal patterns from multivariate time series, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. 

- cs.DB (Databases): The paper proposes a new method for temporal pattern mining, which involves processing large amounts of data. This makes it relevant to the databases sub-category. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper deals with a supervised learning problem, which involves predicting patterns from time series data. This makes it relevant to the machine learning sub-category. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a new method for mining complex patterns, which involves reasoning and decision-making. This makes it relevant to the artificial intelligence sub-category. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper introduces a novel data structure called the Extended Vertical List, which is used to track positions of the first state of the pattern inside records. This makes it relevant to the data structures and algorithms sub-category. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper deals with the problem of mining patterns from time series data, which is relevant to the information retrieval sub-category.
